INSERT INTO profile_scenario_responses (id, profile_id, scenario_id, response, reasoning_chain, emotional_arc, confidence, generation_run_id) VALUES
('65c054d1-1929-4f5d-873b-ca4d686f52fa', 'a520f70a-c96e-4348-bd9f-60a67fb0dc4b', 'ab70d52d-1b81-4bbd-b77a-445d2ac5ddd5', 'Faced with this, this person fires back before fully thinking it through, and true to form discounts the older pattern in favor of whatever just happened.', 'Commits fast to end the tension, treating a quick wrong move as better than a slow right one. An audience is watching how this gets handled.', 'An immediate jolt of alarm, resolving into paralysis — that leaves a residue of vigilance well past the event itself.', 0.51, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('b2c9a626-e551-4e3b-a9c4-8068f0e26307', '78051271-fa13-4520-aee8-3892044881ba', 'e8ab3f18-6112-464e-ac5c-7a8a1f8e1cb5', 'Faced with this, this profile frames the response so it can be walked back later if needed, and true to form remembers every surprise as something they saw coming all along.', 'Keeps expanding the list of scenarios to consider until diminishing returns finally force a stop. An audience is watching how this gets handled.', 'The faintest tightening, gone as soon as it is noticed, resolving into stoic freeze — that is essentially forgotten by the next decision.', 0.76, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('31918f3c-3e3a-4b30-8b2c-fe75816d298c', 'e2fe2afd-2051-401d-a33d-992e0d4d4d64', '9c6ed075-ab1e-4217-a8a6-3fe809880858', 'Faced with this, this profile accepts blame in advance in exchange for the authority to act now, and true to form abandons a private read the instant the crowd leans the other way.', 'Treats the choice as a small research problem: gather the knowable facts first, model the downside, then commit only once the math stops moving. The clock is compressing a decision that would normally take longer.', 'A noticeable but manageable spike of unease, resolving into aggressive counter — that fades within the hour once the decision is locked in.', 0.59, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('f9be38ad-d84e-4b77-8f21-3ff6aa9f9588', '2e9b5fd3-1192-4e5e-807e-fbc9d8796c62', 'a4d80feb-a556-4e78-809c-cf16d873487a', 'Faced with this, this profile accepts the first workable offer rather than sit with more back-and-forth, and true to form is most certain precisely where their competence is thinnest.', 'Picks the option that resolves the discomfort of choosing fastest, then adapts to whatever follows. Every option here also has to survive the other side''s reaction.', 'A sharp initial spike of dread, resolving into paralysis — that lingers and colors the aftermath long after the moment passes.', 0.46, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('e88b13af-92ec-48ba-9412-41baa40a0d02', 'dac25c57-f6d0-4ce3-bebc-a1305b2a4678', 'd069b831-9b5e-495e-9ca5-9d7172f27e2c', 'Faced with this, this type acts on the first strong feeling, hitting the button before the reasoning fully forms, and true to form extrapolates the last data point into a permanent trend.', 'Lets a fast, holistic read override any slower counting of pros and cons that might contradict it. This time the variable is money moving in real time.', 'A brief flicker of tension, resolving into aggressive counter — that fades within the hour once the decision is locked in.', 0.61, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('a57acfd5-f47a-4d87-9f66-8a6d6c102b41', '36b97d54-bbbe-4350-9733-9424f10efee5', '061d80bb-4634-4749-acdc-8f48a4990fb5', 'Faced with this, this type responds in the heat of it, unfiltered, and true to form abandons a private read the instant the crowd leans the other way.', 'Weighs its own instinct as only one input among several trusted others, and defers when they disagree. An audience is watching how this gets handled.', 'A flash of heat that cools almost immediately, resolving into defiant doubling — that settles once the choice is made.', 0.51, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('1560e5a4-0b29-42b5-8032-d27e1a21c169', '733da6b3-43a5-41d0-b3e5-db585c64af5e', '0561a7be-36d3-4c3a-9e17-a5c1771d296d', 'Faced with this, this person confronts it head-on, naming the problem in the room regardless of who bristles, and true to form treats being left out of a move as its own kind of loss.', 'Recognizes the shape of the situation from past experience before consciously naming why, then acts on that recognition. An audience is watching how this gets handled.', 'An instant lurch in the stomach, resolving into panic selling — that leaves a residue of vigilance well past the event itself.', 0.53, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('12c1b5e9-65f7-4e22-8ff4-baf42099de72', '929b6e6b-8c39-426c-9751-7dd855d323f5', 'b36ecd22-d79a-4fbf-ad8d-e3821823da7f', 'Faced with this, this person frames the response so it can be walked back later if needed, and true to form never quite escapes the first figure it heard, however arbitrary.', 'Revisits the same decision from a new angle each time doubt resurfaces, even after nominally deciding. Whatever happens next becomes part of the story people tell about it.', 'Barely a ripple of concern, resolving into stoic freeze — that resolves almost before it registers.', 0.66, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('25a939f8-2d92-4389-835a-3858cd5a7d79', '6d1ffe1f-6e4d-4e07-aaac-377e8e46bbd0', '9c6ed075-ab1e-4217-a8a6-3fe809880858', 'Faced with this, this type makes the call alone rather than wait for consensus that will not arrive in time, and true to form cannot see the gap in its own knowledge from inside the gap.', 'Acts on the strongest immediate impulse and treats hesitation as its own kind of risk. Getting this wrong in public is worse than getting it wrong quietly.', 'A rush of adrenaline that narrows focus fast, resolving into aggressive counter — that gets relived and replayed long after it stops being useful.', 0.53, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('397247d3-85ae-4257-8ac6-af6e955049b0', '5a277381-d43d-4319-8c92-e8ef8b3c3693', '4a249520-c605-49c1-a240-b1daa5dad39c', 'Faced with this, the individual builds a rapid decision tree and works it in order, ignoring the noise around it, and true to form prices every token against its all-time high, viewing current levels as an automatic discount.', 'Breaks the decision into weighted criteria before looking at gut feel, and lets the tally overrule any single strong reaction. There is no version of this where every stakeholder ends up satisfied.', 'A flat, measured pulse with no real spike, resolving into stoic freeze — that resolves almost before it registers.', 0.73, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('9a1b16d1-e2d2-4f90-a32a-6bb981938072', '2fbc3fb5-304e-49c4-a1f8-add86bd729ce', 'b7292be8-538d-4231-abb0-8ca9ed0df187', 'Faced with this, the individual makes the call alone rather than wait for consensus that will not arrive in time, and true to form jumps into whatever everyone else already seems to be winning at.', 'Trusts a felt sense of pattern over any spreadsheet, treating hesitation itself as evidence something is off. There is no version of this where every stakeholder ends up satisfied.', 'A quick surge of adrenaline that fades as fast as it came, resolving into righteous anger — that resolves as soon as there is something concrete to act on.', 0.55, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('155e20ae-365e-463d-9f92-e41fe594d496', '0ad3af2b-b1f5-4e85-a427-28c5eda41f0c', '9198a4cb-3900-4d8d-b9db-e77dec914c8e', 'Faced with this, the individual takes the contrarian side deliberately, willing to be early and wrong before being right, and true to form extrapolates the last data point into a permanent trend.', 'Trusts the first workable idea enough to move on it before a second one can compete for attention. Price action does not care which argument feels more convincing.', 'A sharp initial spike of dread, resolving into paralysis — that gets relived and replayed long after it stops being useful.', 0.49, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('cc2615d3-ba73-4d4e-9787-3f4ceca309c4', '3f227fd9-5ccb-40db-ba83-70e995cdd83b', '1fbde86b-6e35-47a3-9549-7b925f13a51e', 'Faced with this, the individual stays silent past the point of discomfort, letting the other side fill the gap, and true to form underestimates how often an obviously right call turns out wrong.', 'Treats the choice as a small research problem: gather the knowable facts first, model the downside, then commit only once the math stops moving. The counterparty is reading every hesitation as information.', 'A flat, measured pulse with no real spike, resolving into relief capitulation — that never really rises to the level of a feeling at all.', 0.87, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('02919950-9c09-492f-a6ca-77939d735011', 'ddf347b2-55ec-4fe2-a2a4-069ed1dc1adf', '040c060d-e8ab-44dd-bc51-87a9448efd53', 'Faced with this, this profile treats the incident as a sequence of small decisions rather than one big one, and true to form remembers every surprise as something they saw coming all along.', 'Revisits the same decision from a new angle each time doubt resurfaces, even after nominally deciding. Getting this wrong in public is worse than getting it wrong quietly.', 'A flat, measured pulse with no real spike, resolving into euphoric overreach — that resolves almost before it registers.', 0.73, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('8c7f83b3-1f87-470f-b035-da054735c7b6', '35154386-7b88-4e18-8f14-122583fe9d12', 'c253ce52-8aff-4d32-8501-df152008772e', 'Faced with this, this type takes command and acts decisively, accepting personal risk to move faster than the situation, and true to form is most certain precisely where their competence is thinnest.', 'Skips the formal weighing entirely — the answer arrives whole, and the reasoning is reconstructed only if someone asks for it. The clock is compressing a decision that would normally take longer.', 'A quick surge of adrenaline that fades as fast as it came, resolving into righteous anger — that fades within the hour once the decision is locked in.', 0.57, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('468c0412-70f8-430c-8d36-269f984a8485', 'f37fe64b-1813-425a-af5b-13ae41f30d61', '9198a4cb-3900-4d8d-b9db-e77dec914c8e', 'Faced with this, this type reacts to the headline before confirming it, then scrambles to justify the trade after, and true to form treats being left out of a move as its own kind of loss.', 'Picks the option that resolves the discomfort of choosing fastest, then adapts to whatever follows. This time the variable is money moving in real time.', 'An instant lurch in the stomach, resolving into anxious spiral — that keeps resurfacing in quiet moments for days afterward.', 0.45, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('f591bf4d-e9db-4f7f-a156-e5a5f90c5af3', 'd05d2455-9407-480d-953a-eb3f61bfe442', 'a239ba25-b49b-4d8d-b75e-c59e1730a283', 'Faced with this, this type stays silent past the point of discomfort, letting the other side fill the gap, and true to form remembers every surprise as something they saw coming all along.', 'Distrusts the first plausible-sounding answer and keeps testing alternatives until one survives every objection raised against it. Every option here also has to survive the other side''s reaction.', 'The faintest tightening, gone as soon as it is noticed, resolving into euphoric overreach — that is essentially forgotten by the next decision.', 0.69, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('453223d0-d286-4379-abb4-1063100fe5ab', 'ad2d66d0-71df-4c04-b4db-e32f4100d4ec', '0561a7be-36d3-4c3a-9e17-a5c1771d296d', 'Faced with this, this type weighs the audience as carefully as the actual disagreement, and true to form remembers every surprise as something they saw coming all along.', 'Treats a rushed decision as a defect regardless of outcome, and resists pressure to shortcut the process. The social cost and the practical cost point in different directions.', 'A flash of heat that cools almost immediately, resolving into defiant doubling — that settles once the choice is made.', 0.68, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('aac5fa4e-f56c-4daa-acd1-66c5f13dbffd', '090d58a6-7d4f-44ae-9dde-cbd779c206ea', 'a239ba25-b49b-4d8d-b75e-c59e1730a283', 'Faced with this, this profile accepts the first workable offer rather than sit with more back-and-forth, and true to form discounts their own exposure to the risks they warn others about.', 'Delays a final answer until at least one credible outside opinion has weighed in, treating solo conviction as insufficient. The counterparty is reading every hesitation as information.', 'A quick surge of adrenaline that fades as fast as it came, resolving into righteous anger — that dissolves quickly once the ambiguity clears.', 0.54, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('8c515f9e-2977-4bba-bc6c-656ee4015760', 'd602faf3-bb40-49f4-90e9-f7c420992cf3', '47a49b31-caca-4e61-b2d6-45e7595d4fae', 'Faced with this, this type builds a rapid decision tree and works it in order, ignoring the noise around it, and true to form expects to be the exception to a risk it can otherwise describe accurately.', 'Revisits the same decision from a new angle each time doubt resurfaces, even after nominally deciding. Getting this wrong in public is worse than getting it wrong quietly.', 'Almost no visible reaction at all, resolving into performative calm — that resolves almost before it registers.', 0.66, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('c0390f29-3cfd-409b-85f1-ee7a2c555b54', '24f99b2e-7359-4ce5-954c-bce9acf4b7d1', '5c273a7c-8072-45b3-bc41-5808c1d1d1a8', 'Faced with this, this person walks from the table on principle, trusting the other side to come back, and true to form exits winning positions at the first minor delay or quiet period from devs.', 'Trusts the first workable idea enough to move on it before a second one can compete for attention. The relationship and the number are both on the table at once.', 'An instant lurch in the stomach, resolving into dissociative deferral — that gets relived and replayed long after it stops being useful.', 0.5, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('201ecc0b-a48f-4e24-8839-0b84a61568da', '103e366b-2738-4671-b454-592ab59dc50a', 'b7292be8-538d-4231-abb0-8ca9ed0df187', 'Faced with this, this profile moves before the full picture is in, unable to tolerate the uncertainty, and true to form gains confidence in a position in proportion to how many others hold it.', 'Weighs its own instinct as only one input among several trusted others, and defers when they disagree. There is no version of this where every stakeholder ends up satisfied.', 'A brief flicker of tension, resolving into aggressive counter — that resolves as soon as there is something concrete to act on.', 0.54, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('643baed2-83e2-484f-a70b-86e56802a237', '66f4802b-2b33-4aa8-8c95-28ba8945dc91', '35b9f838-186d-4475-9d51-c276aa620e73', 'Faced with this, this type scales in aggressively, judging the crowd''s fear as the better signal to fade, and true to form jumps into whatever everyone else already seems to be winning at.', 'Skips the formal weighing entirely — the answer arrives whole, and the reasoning is reconstructed only if someone asks for it. Price action does not care which argument feels more convincing.', 'A brief flicker of tension, resolving into fomo buying — that fades within the hour once the decision is locked in.', 0.55, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('00fe73a7-3538-499c-98fa-0fa89c5783dc', '7016f2ca-ed45-4e04-b7ea-4d804cd75daf', 'ab70d52d-1b81-4bbd-b77a-445d2ac5ddd5', 'Faced with this, this profile responds deliberately, choosing words to protect their standing without escalating, and true to form lets the first number on the table quietly set the whole range.', 'Distrusts the first plausible-sounding answer and keeps testing alternatives until one survives every objection raised against it. Whatever happens next becomes part of the story people tell about it.', 'A brief flicker of tension, resolving into appeasement — that fades within the hour once the decision is locked in.', 0.65, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('6fd43834-f230-459b-9a70-8ecb6d605e69', '11d24c12-3b58-4766-973b-abd387209a22', '297fb91d-46c7-49a9-b4d0-ba6ec4c25b3a', 'Faced with this, the individual responds deliberately, choosing words to protect their standing without escalating, and true to form prices every token against its all-time high, viewing current levels as an automatic discount.', 'Reads the situation in a single gut pass, locks onto the option that "feels" right, and assembles the justification afterward. The social cost and the practical cost point in different directions.', 'The faintest tightening, gone as soon as it is noticed, resolving into euphoric overreach — that resolves almost before it registers.', 0.66, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('6b26c0db-2913-4b9d-b0be-5233c3a5e3cb', '3a2179ae-9158-49c8-9766-945b5ce546b1', '5926adc5-d8c7-4ed7-b3d4-bb7a1d451a87', 'Faced with this, the individual responds deliberately, choosing words to protect their standing without escalating, and true to form is surprised in the moment and certain in the retelling.', 'Revisits the same decision from a new angle each time doubt resurfaces, even after nominally deciding. The social cost and the practical cost point in different directions.', 'Almost no visible reaction at all, resolving into performative calm — that is essentially forgotten by the next decision.', 0.72, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('cf8a910f-9173-412d-a6db-974d0d34c9c0', '9658ee2a-ccc3-4eba-9fd9-21d8043f109b', '11ae3fa4-a23c-48b0-9bed-741e8b6f4007', 'Faced with this, this type offers a face-saving off-ramp for the other side even at some cost to itself, and true to form refuses to exit positions until price returns to the previous cycle peak.', 'Keeps expanding the list of scenarios to consider until diminishing returns finally force a stop. The counterparty is reading every hesitation as information.', 'The faintest tightening, gone as soon as it is noticed, resolving into euphoric overreach — that never really rises to the level of a feeling at all.', 0.7, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('e370a6c2-77e4-49bc-a2be-c7cfad289db2', '8674908f-1fc8-435b-96ea-f5a662febd25', '5b22dd1d-712f-4728-883a-247c094d1f40', 'Faced with this, this profile takes the contrarian side deliberately, willing to be early and wrong before being right, and true to form assumes the bad statistic applies to other people.', 'Lets urgency substitute for analysis, converting pressure directly into action. Price action does not care which argument feels more convincing.', 'A quick surge of adrenaline that fades as fast as it came, resolving into appeasement — that settles once the choice is made.', 0.66, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('1e2cbcc9-048d-4259-8ee9-6bee40b0a369', '67310190-97ba-44f7-9cea-bc35f058bf14', '428eedc0-a3a5-4f70-8c25-0ab71ee0a6be', 'Faced with this, this type softens the ask to keep the conversation moving rather than risk a stall, and true to form rewrites its own uncertainty out of the story after the fact.', 'Walks every branch and contingency in sequence, uneasy until the residual ambiguity is as small as it can be. The counterparty is reading every hesitation as information.', 'Almost no visible reaction at all, resolving into performative calm — that leaves no discernible trace once the moment passes.', 0.66, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
