('e2860eb3-75f4-4ba8-aad5-3a7ae5e96952', 'e76bdfa3-712f-4619-b7e3-b9daffc5a0f3', '41f7d449-0ae6-4652-a158-df8912159433', 'Faced with this, this profile scales in aggressively, judging the crowd''s fear as the better signal to fade, and true to form jumps into whatever everyone else already seems to be winning at.', 'Acts on the strongest immediate impulse and treats hesitation as its own kind of risk. Price action does not care which argument feels more convincing.', 'A noticeable but manageable spike of unease, resolving into fomo buying — that fades within the hour once the decision is locked in.', 0.6, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('3a629fd3-cfef-420a-81d3-a97535eae370', '981de27f-cae8-4390-bf0b-2cf9bfd5ecdf', '41f7d449-0ae6-4652-a158-df8912159433', 'Faced with this, this person runs the scenario through a checklist built in advance and follows wherever it points, and true to form prices every token against its all-time high, viewing current levels as an automatic discount.', 'Keeps expanding the list of scenarios to consider until diminishing returns finally force a stop. Price action does not care which argument feels more convincing.', 'A flat, measured pulse with no real spike, resolving into cold calculation — that is essentially forgotten by the next decision.', 0.7, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('827b39fa-8a9a-4ec8-bee2-597c5a3515ec', 'da1302c5-d044-400d-974b-36b5c9f80173', '9f05bc0d-6774-495f-b2e3-787f6be7b98e', 'Faced with this, this profile presses the position further, treating the volatility itself as the opportunity, and true to form discounts the older pattern in favor of whatever just happened.', 'Reads the situation in a single gut pass, locks onto the option that "feels" right, and assembles the justification afterward. Price action does not care which argument feels more convincing.', 'A quick surge of adrenaline that fades as fast as it came, resolving into vindication seeking — that dissolves quickly once the ambiguity clears.', 0.53, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('e3c61164-e842-48c8-83e8-d228a9a41d26', '0efa6d35-2dba-49bd-8995-274e4215b2d8', '9e53db37-83cd-4d10-a159-ae3e0abef3d2', 'Faced with this, this person agrees on the spot to end the tension, details to be sorted out later, and true to form finds it easier to believe something once it stops being a minority view.', 'Weighs its own instinct as only one input among several trusted others, and defers when they disagree. The counterparty is reading every hesitation as information.', 'A flash of heat that cools almost immediately, resolving into fomo buying — that dissolves quickly once the ambiguity clears.', 0.57, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('03ca83c2-a93b-41b6-aa15-4752983f7519', '733da6b3-43a5-41d0-b3e5-db585c64af5e', '5b22dd1d-712f-4728-883a-247c094d1f40', 'Faced with this, this profile takes the contrarian side deliberately, willing to be early and wrong before being right, and true to form treats being left out of a move as its own kind of loss.', 'Trusts a felt sense of pattern over any spreadsheet, treating hesitation itself as evidence something is off. This time the variable is money moving in real time.', 'A rush of adrenaline that narrows focus fast, resolving into panic selling — that lingers and colors the aftermath long after the moment passes.', 0.47, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c')
INSERT INTO profile_scenario_responses (id, profile_id, scenario_id, response, reasoning_chain, emotional_arc, confidence, generation_run_id) VALUES
('573ecd65-fcf0-4c31-9aea-ff358a172456', '5e632d34-fbbe-4884-9066-0c703f9acbf9', '1ab17fff-6628-44a9-add9-8345c3b372ed', 'Faced with this, the individual tracks concessions explicitly and matches them one-for-one, never more, and true to form discounts the older pattern in favor of whatever just happened.', 'Distrusts the first plausible-sounding answer and keeps testing alternatives until one survives every objection raised against it. The counterparty is reading every hesitation as information.', 'A flat, measured pulse with no real spike, resolving into cold calculation — that is essentially forgotten by the next decision.', 0.68, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('79a41d5d-b907-45c3-a4f0-65a2b911e430', '0bc388ae-8758-4761-8ebe-bfc4a1213706', 'd069b831-9b5e-495e-9ca5-9d7172f27e2c', 'Faced with this, this profile reacts to the headline before confirming it, then scrambles to justify the trade after, and true to form guards against losses far more fiercely than they chase equivalent gains.', 'Buries the hard call under a pile of preparatory busywork that never quite finishes. The numbers on the screen are the only feedback that matters here.', 'An immediate jolt of alarm, resolving into dissociative deferral — that lingers and colors the aftermath long after the moment passes.', 0.48, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('5acd0a42-2ab6-4d1c-9e19-28d73ba2b1f4', 'ff4af631-1397-47a2-bed3-427d4e747a8d', 'b0442052-e912-4df5-a983-405a686c1ec8', 'Faced with this, this profile triages coldly, sequencing the least-reversible decisions first and documenting each step, and true to form underestimates how often an obviously right call turns out wrong.', 'Lays out the options explicitly, assigns each a rough expected value, and picks the one that survives the numbers — distrusting any impulse that cannot be written down. Getting this wrong in public is worse than getting it wrong quietly.', 'The faintest tightening, gone as soon as it is noticed, resolving into stoic freeze — that resolves almost before it registers.', 0.92, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('f057478a-d20e-4464-a0a2-ef9715e41799', '96b03ad9-14b7-4365-b8a2-6b8f4098897f', '5926adc5-d8c7-4ed7-b3d4-bb7a1d451a87', 'Faced with this, this type frames the response so it can be walked back later if needed, and true to form is more certain than the hit rate justifies.', 'Distrusts the first plausible-sounding answer and keeps testing alternatives until one survives every objection raised against it. An audience is watching how this gets handled.', 'A brief flicker of tension, resolving into defiant doubling — that resolves as soon as there is something concrete to act on.', 0.88, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('fda23848-60d9-45e7-b9af-800f3a051cef', 'e62d2dd8-f865-4045-8dd2-04a0fbfedb3b', '1ce15a3d-2b5d-41c6-a304-47d4f2e54e85', 'Faced with this, this person tracks concessions explicitly and matches them one-for-one, never more, and true to form remembers every surprise as something they saw coming all along.', 'Separates the emotional read from the analytical one on purpose, writes both down, and lets the analytical read win the tiebreak. The counterparty is reading every hesitation as information.', 'Barely a ripple of concern, resolving into euphoric overreach — that is essentially forgotten by the next decision.', 0.72, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('11e25299-07eb-4821-90e5-71c64badcb16', '698f62f3-5a7a-49f4-a3a4-541ae6df8b2c', '7fa3857a-8ae5-479c-a7da-f1bc75f51a95', 'Faced with this, this person acts on the first plausible fix without checking for a better one, and true to form cannot watch a rally from the sidelines for long.', 'Picks the option that resolves the discomfort of choosing fastest, then adapts to whatever follows. There is no version of this where every stakeholder ends up satisfied.', 'A rush of adrenaline that narrows focus fast, resolving into fomo buying — that gets relived and replayed long after it stops being useful.', 0.5, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('a037f801-3eca-4f14-b75c-3234e8ca79ae', 'c987804f-6f72-402b-9e64-a3aeb073bff8', '7b6f37f5-c76e-46ea-8169-21f32e56ec9c', 'Faced with this, the individual treats the incident as a sequence of small decisions rather than one big one, and true to form treats past peak valuation as guaranteed future recovery.', 'Distrusts the first plausible-sounding answer and keeps testing alternatives until one survives every objection raised against it. Getting this wrong in public is worse than getting it wrong quietly.', 'Something closer to mild interest than alarm, resolving into cold calculation — that leaves no discernible trace once the moment passes.', 0.73, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('425fda75-e347-4d80-badd-1d29076e8e87', '40da97fc-63d0-4eea-af1a-33f64dcb867b', 'a4d80feb-a556-4e78-809c-cf16d873487a', 'Faced with this, this profile counters aggressively, re-anchoring hard and daring the other side to walk, and true to form extrapolates the last data point into a permanent trend.', 'Prefers a decisive wrong turn to an open-ended maybe, and corrects course later if it has to. Every option here also has to survive the other side''s reaction.', 'A momentary tightening before the response settles, resolving into appeasement — that fades within the hour once the decision is locked in.', 0.55, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('a3d9026b-8c8b-470b-876c-4c083726b22e', 'd0d03b56-e626-4f07-8d7b-540a51e96b47', 'b7e8326d-2e3d-438b-9a4a-989a27a339c9', 'Faced with this, this person treats the moment as one more data point for a system, not an exception to react to, and true to form expects to be the exception to a risk it can otherwise describe accurately.', 'Walks every branch and contingency in sequence, uneasy until the residual ambiguity is as small as it can be. This time the variable is money moving in real time.', 'Barely a ripple of concern, resolving into cold calculation — that leaves no discernible trace once the moment passes.', 0.71, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
