('a11aa694-d15f-4eb6-b913-0c6c0ad22479', 'b87661af-5403-4774-9f2c-a3eaffa0a010', '4a249520-c605-49c1-a240-b1daa5dad39c', 'Faced with this, the individual treats the incident as a sequence of small decisions rather than one big one, and true to form is more certain than the hit rate justifies.', 'Distrusts the first plausible-sounding answer and keeps testing alternatives until one survives every objection raised against it. There is no version of this where every stakeholder ends up satisfied.', 'Almost no visible reaction at all, resolving into relief capitulation — that is essentially forgotten by the next decision.', 0.82, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('7c4ed8e0-748c-4ac0-9e40-dade4678174a', 'c9d1d11f-999d-49db-8b69-09559503eac0', '3f16a2c2-b990-4db8-9f26-5f0e1df34dfb', 'Faced with this, the individual calls it out publicly rather than let it pass unaddressed, and true to form finds it hard to hold a contrarian position once the room disagrees.', 'Reads the situation in a single gut pass, locks onto the option that "feels" right, and assembles the justification afterward. Whatever happens next becomes part of the story people tell about it.', 'A noticeable but manageable spike of unease, resolving into appeasement — that fades within the hour once the decision is locked in.', 0.58, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('318fc459-ec84-4b32-87d1-f480e556d120', 'd103880b-7c91-4463-9406-7ce75689d688', 'b7292be8-538d-4231-abb0-8ca9ed0df187', 'Faced with this, this profile accepts blame in advance in exchange for the authority to act now, and true to form treats non-refundable network fees as active position cost basis.', 'Lets urgency substitute for analysis, converting pressure directly into action. There is no version of this where every stakeholder ends up satisfied.', 'A noticeable but manageable spike of unease, resolving into aggressive counter — that dissolves quickly once the ambiguity clears.', 0.6, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('907a5138-75eb-4996-8431-d43dbfc654a7', '67fb4ed9-91b0-47d9-9a76-1f81e13f74c2', '973e025e-78e9-40f5-be8d-5ebe7983517c', 'Faced with this, the individual triages coldly, sequencing the least-reversible decisions first and documenting each step, and true to form discounts the older pattern in favor of whatever just happened.', 'Builds an explicit decision matrix for a call most people would make on instinct, and defers to whichever option scores highest even if it feels wrong. Getting this wrong in public is worse than getting it wrong quietly.', 'A flat, measured pulse with no real spike, resolving into relief capitulation — that never really rises to the level of a feeling at all.', 0.71, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('a19cba00-be5f-46e7-a59f-f4b1193891f9', '456dd90c-06df-4e43-8fd1-72729ba5f063', '09012784-e9fd-4c1a-9bca-012c91055bcc', 'Faced with this, this type escalates the demand mid-conversation on impulse, surprising even itself, and true to form feels a winning position as fragile and a losing one as merely paused.', 'Keeps every option notionally open as long as possible, even at the cost of the best ones expiring first. The relationship and the number are both on the table at once.', 'A rush of adrenaline that narrows focus fast, resolving into fomo buying — that leaves a residue of vigilance well past the event itself.', 0.44, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('1437e8c2-435c-4170-b8e4-755dfb4b0b39', '222b8eaf-e6fa-4995-aa7c-a21ec9f038f4', '7b6f37f5-c76e-46ea-8169-21f32e56ec9c', 'Faced with this, this profile lunges at the most visible fix, trading a fast intervention for a considered one, and true to form delays checking the number it most needs to check.', 'Keeps every option notionally open as long as possible, even at the cost of the best ones expiring first. Getting this wrong in public is worse than getting it wrong quietly.', 'An immediate jolt of alarm, resolving into anxious spiral — that gets relived and replayed long after it stops being useful.', 0.6, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('2327ce41-2391-4596-9459-be63d7c905f0', '17aaf66b-be4c-4743-86e5-9be0b9fc2f6a', 'b78c70d1-7d9a-4e52-874d-655d87ddce5b', 'Faced with this, this profile isolates the irreversible choices and makes those first, deferring the rest, and true to form treats past peak valuation as guaranteed future recovery.', 'Treats a rushed decision as a defect regardless of outcome, and resists pressure to shortcut the process. The clock is compressing a decision that would normally take longer.', 'Something closer to mild interest than alarm, resolving into performative calm — that resolves almost before it registers.', 0.75, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('241b2f83-b8a6-44ad-bff1-7db6d443154d', '37201646-133b-47be-b2ca-19edeeeb5e4c', '8df0d1ba-9b00-437a-92c5-4301263555f6', 'Faced with this, this type stays silent past the point of discomfort, letting the other side fill the gap, and true to form discounts their own exposure to the risks they warn others about.', 'Builds an explicit decision matrix for a call most people would make on instinct, and defers to whichever option scores highest even if it feels wrong. The counterparty is reading every hesitation as information.', 'A flat, measured pulse with no real spike, resolving into cold calculation — that leaves no discernible trace once the moment passes.', 0.71, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('caa4dd34-d73a-4625-9eba-e9c36307a26f', '1c991865-37c9-4ac2-886a-4e77f7ff4060', '47a49b31-caca-4e61-b2d6-45e7595d4fae', 'Faced with this, the individual moves before the full picture is in, unable to tolerate the uncertainty, and true to form mistakes a little fluency for real mastery.', 'Commits fast to end the tension, treating a quick wrong move as better than a slow right one. There is no version of this where every stakeholder ends up satisfied.', 'A rush of adrenaline that narrows focus fast, resolving into dissociative deferral — that leaves a residue of vigilance well past the event itself.', 0.5, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('558fa26e-997c-4c56-87fa-6e744ecbf94e', '0e01f05f-cbe5-490e-9a9b-a9ac87477e14', '7fa3857a-8ae5-479c-a7da-f1bc75f51a95', 'Faced with this, this type treats the incident as a sequence of small decisions rather than one big one, and true to form prices every token against its all-time high, viewing current levels as an automatic discount.', 'Revisits the same decision from a new angle each time doubt resurfaces, even after nominally deciding. Getting this wrong in public is worse than getting it wrong quietly.', 'Barely a ripple of concern, resolving into relief capitulation — that is essentially forgotten by the next decision.', 0.75, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c')
INSERT INTO profile_scenario_responses (id, profile_id, scenario_id, response, reasoning_chain, emotional_arc, confidence, generation_run_id) VALUES
('d54b8f57-91fe-4ec7-81d0-cc718cf712ad', '47096246-1211-4188-8b8f-94928058694f', '5cd45a74-f2a6-46cc-bd9d-b50abbe66a9b', 'Faced with this, this profile responds deliberately, choosing words to protect their standing without escalating, and true to form measures protocol loyalty by historical gas spent rather than current utility.', 'Breaks the decision into weighted criteria before looking at gut feel, and lets the tally overrule any single strong reaction. An audience is watching how this gets handled.', 'A momentary tightening before the response settles, resolving into fomo buying — that fades within the hour once the decision is locked in.', 0.68, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('d4f86127-be3b-4384-86f4-47c6de2c5f3f', '18fd80b6-ccf3-416e-9ec5-8d52db40a9a0', 'e1fdcaee-3b02-4815-aec1-be30f6877b6d', 'Faced with this, this type executes the pre-committed plan exactly, resisting the urge to improvise under pressure, and true to form underestimates how often an obviously right call turns out wrong.', 'Treats the choice as a small research problem: gather the knowable facts first, model the downside, then commit only once the math stops moving. The numbers on the screen are the only feedback that matters here.', 'Barely a ripple of concern, resolving into relief capitulation — that never really rises to the level of a feeling at all.', 0.92, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('b28479a1-bb13-4f3d-8f81-c2ae666524c4', 'b3bfb2f0-d3c2-476f-a4d8-7e6084889079', '14f418f6-9487-4459-bdee-98cb8bc6a7b6', 'Faced with this, this type weighs the audience as carefully as the actual disagreement, and true to form refuses to exit positions until price returns to the previous cycle peak.', 'Slow-walks the decision through every foreseeable consequence before allowing itself to commit. The social cost and the practical cost point in different directions.', 'The faintest tightening, gone as soon as it is noticed, resolving into euphoric overreach — that resolves almost before it registers.', 0.72, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('4c254dc5-0dc1-40a1-8c30-d78b2bbdc752', '73139ba9-4320-42fb-8f28-43b5888ddd7e', '5926adc5-d8c7-4ed7-b3d4-bb7a1d451a87', 'Faced with this, the individual frames the response so it can be walked back later if needed, and true to form expects to be the exception to a risk it can otherwise describe accurately.', 'Treats the choice as a small research problem: gather the knowable facts first, model the downside, then commit only once the math stops moving. An audience is watching how this gets handled.', 'Almost no visible reaction at all, resolving into euphoric overreach — that leaves no discernible trace once the moment passes.', 0.74, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('d8f0d400-0ea2-47d8-afc5-2991ceca9071', '1da8a242-f806-4065-9ea8-988a62bef51b', '0561a7be-36d3-4c3a-9e17-a5c1771d296d', 'Faced with this, this person responds in the heat of it, unfiltered, and true to form jumps into whatever everyone else already seems to be winning at.', 'Reads the situation in a single gut pass, locks onto the option that "feels" right, and assembles the justification afterward. An audience is watching how this gets handled.', 'A sharp initial spike of dread, resolving into aggressive counter — that leaves a residue of vigilance well past the event itself.', 0.52, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('0cfe19ea-85ab-4416-b1aa-99a9041a3f38', 'be9b39db-0f6a-4d80-8e52-23415d0a162d', '4a249520-c605-49c1-a240-b1daa5dad39c', 'Faced with this, this type moves before the full picture is in, unable to tolerate the uncertainty, and true to form looks away from bad news in the hope it resolves unwitnessed.', 'Prefers a decisive wrong turn to an open-ended maybe, and corrects course later if it has to. Getting this wrong in public is worse than getting it wrong quietly.', 'An immediate jolt of alarm, resolving into guilt absorption — that leaves a residue of vigilance well past the event itself.', 0.51, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('69b8357e-f385-4ac2-bf1b-484f6654a678', 'e9be4384-7759-4371-9c4e-8fcfcf0f9b9c', '5cd45a74-f2a6-46cc-bd9d-b50abbe66a9b', 'Faced with this, this type defers the confrontation to a calmer, more private moment, and true to form rewrites its own uncertainty out of the story after the fact.', 'Treats a rushed decision as a defect regardless of outcome, and resists pressure to shortcut the process. The social cost and the practical cost point in different directions.', 'A flash of heat that cools almost immediately, resolving into aggressive counter — that dissolves quickly once the ambiguity clears.', 0.63, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('9b6cb5fe-0b80-4119-80e7-1f2c240a7805', 'f3d595f3-817b-450d-a4d9-89ec2c7567d3', 'd069b831-9b5e-495e-9ca5-9d7172f27e2c', 'Faced with this, this type executes the pre-committed plan exactly, resisting the urge to improvise under pressure, and true to form is more certain than the hit rate justifies.', 'Treats the choice as a small research problem: gather the knowable facts first, model the downside, then commit only once the math stops moving. This time the variable is money moving in real time.', 'A brief flicker of tension, resolving into aggressive counter — that settles once the choice is made.', 0.74, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('937d6008-1e93-44c1-8e3d-8cce2c756ec4', '10160d76-785e-41e3-b9bf-923177bd46ec', '624fe45e-c108-4588-9e1c-c45b46436540', 'Faced with this, the individual runs the scenario through a checklist built in advance and follows wherever it points, and true to form remembers every surprise as something they saw coming all along.', 'Wants the decision to survive hindsight, not just produce a good outcome, so it over-invests in the reasoning itself. The numbers on the screen are the only feedback that matters here.', 'Something closer to mild interest than alarm, resolving into euphoric overreach — that leaves no discernible trace once the moment passes.', 0.75, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
