('ff2835eb-e03f-41da-96cc-b7f954361f6a', 'f37fe64b-1813-425a-af5b-13ae41f30d61', 'e623b62f-275f-4641-b1a8-338b678c7fae', 'Faced with this, this person chases the move in real time, adjusting size on gut feel as the price ticks, and true to form cannot watch a rally from the sidelines for long.', 'Commits fast to end the tension, treating a quick wrong move as better than a slow right one. Price action does not care which argument feels more convincing.', 'An instant lurch in the stomach, resolving into dissociative deferral — that keeps resurfacing in quiet moments for days afterward.', 0.44, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
('4bdb8061-d87d-4597-ba29-95c217a33b93', '42eb9f0b-2170-490f-a1cf-4584f2ed7ecb', '9c6ed075-ab1e-4217-a8a6-3fe809880858', 'Faced with this, this person treats the incident as a sequence of small decisions rather than one big one, and true to form expects to be the exception to a risk it can otherwise describe accurately.', 'Separates the emotional read from the analytical one on purpose, writes both down, and lets the analytical read win the tiebreak. Getting this wrong in public is worse than getting it wrong quietly.', 'Something closer to mild interest than alarm, resolving into performative calm — that never really rises to the level of a feeling at all.', 0.7, '092841db-d88c-438b-ab16-502e8e44c63c'),
